    {
        "content": "<p>I think maybe we should had a <code>rw</code> lemma like <code>If a is a pos real number, then (-a : ℂ)^(1/2 : ℂ) = √a * I</code>.</p>",
        "id": 518808037,
        "sender_full_name": "张守信(Shouxin Zhang)",
        "timestamp": 1747479275
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do we have much API at all for raising complex numbers to complex powers? This is not a well-behaved notion, is it? Why have you ended up wanting to do this? Surely it would be better to raise a complex number to a real power? This is a much better-behaved function.</p>",
        "id": 518810329,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1747481303
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh wait -- we don't even <em>have</em> complex number to real or rational power??</p>",
        "id": 518810377,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1747481373
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110038\">Kevin Buzzard</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/Prove.20that.20.60.28-3.20.3A.20.E2.84.82.29.5E.281.2F2.20.3A.20.E2.84.82.29.20.3D.20.E2.88.9A3.20*.20I.60/near/518810329\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Do we have much API at all for raising complex numbers to complex powers? This is not a well-behaved notion, is it? Why have you ended up wanting to do this? Surely it would be better to raise a complex number to a real power? This is a much better-behaved function.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I want to prove the following example( <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msqrt><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msqrt></mrow></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>−</mo><msqrt><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msqrt></mrow></msqrt><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\sqrt{1+\\sqrt{-3}}+\\sqrt{1-\\sqrt{-3}} = \\sqrt{6}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.24em;vertical-align:-0.2094em;\"></span><span class=\"mord sqrt\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.0306em;\"><span class=\"svg-align\" style=\"top:-3.2em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3.2em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\" style=\"padding-left:1em;\"><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mord sqrt\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8656em;\"><span class=\"svg-align\" style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mor